Major German cities on the water include the massive port city of Hamburg (Elbe River/North Sea), capital city Berlin (Spree/Havel rivers), and coastal hub Kiel on the Baltic Sea. Other prominent cities located along major rivers include Cologne and Düsseldorf (Rhine), while Munich offers significant riverine, lake, and swimming access via the Isar River. 
