Top Big Cities on the Water:
Hamburg (Port City): Connected to the North Sea by the Elbe River, it is Germany’s largest port, featuring extensive canals, the Speicherstadt warehouse district, and a maritime atmosphere.
Berlin (River City): Known for having more bridges than Venice due to the Spree and Havel rivers passing through the city.
Kiel (Baltic Sea): As the capital of Schleswig-Holstein, it is a key coastal city on the Baltic Sea known for sailing and its port.
Cologne & Düsseldorf (Rhine River): Large cities along the Rhine, which is a major commercial waterway in western Germany.
Rostock (Baltic Sea): A historical Baltic city known for its city harbor and maritime history.
Wilhelmshaven (North Sea): Located on the North Sea, it is known as a significant maritime hub with mudflats. 
